msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Alchemical handbook of experiments and recipes. Instructions include transmutation of metals, making a small pearl or gemstone larger, creation of and uses for potable gold, and other elixirs, oils, and tinctures. Recipes includes medicinal applications such as flower remedies for asthma, consumption (p. 357), and dropsie (p. 358).
msContents.textLang: English, with a few pages in French

author.name: Charles Rainsford Collection of Alchemical and Occult Manuscripts (University of Pennsylvania)

supportDesc.extent: 484 leaves : 213 x 185 (165 x 90) mm bound to 226 x 202 mm +
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 484 + i (contemporary paper) leaves; [xxvi], 1-194, 196-614, 596-773, 773-877, 888-913; contemporary pagination in ink, modern pagination in pencil, upper outer corners. All references in this record are to contemporary pagination.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script in the hand of Charles Rainsford (note with initials, front flyleaf verso)..

binding.p: Contemporary gold-tooled leather. Spine leather deteriorating.

origin.p: Written in England in 1797 (note, back flyleaf recto).

history.provenance: Owned by the 2nd through 12th Dukes of Northumberland, ms. 603, Alnwick Castle, Northumberland, 1809-2014 (bookplate, inside upper cover; stamps throughout).
Formerly owned by Charles Rainsford (British army officer, fellow of the Royal Society, and alchemist; stamp, p. xxiv); bequeathed by Rainsford to Hugh Percy, Second Duke of Northumberland.
Sold at auction at Sotheby's (London), 15 July 2014, as part of Lot 411.
